{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_13","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"litehive report --verdict pass --role reviewer --step accepting --message \\\"Accepted. I verified the repo now has tests_integration/ at the root with conftest.py, helpers.py, README.md, __init__.py, and one per-engine file for codex, claude, copilot, gemini, opencode, and goz. Repo inspection confirmed the new suite has zero litehive coupling: ripgrep found no 'from litehive', 'import litehive', or 'LITEHIVE_' references under tests_integration/. The helper layer exercises the intended public adapter seam: get_engine(name) -> build_invocation(...) -> finalize_invocation(...) -> subprocess.run(...) -> render_transcript(...), with continuation extraction via extract_engine_continuation(...). It honors HERU_INTEGRATION_ENGINES and HERU_INTEGRATION_TIMEOUT_SECONDS, skips when opt-in is unset, skips when the binary is absent from PATH, and applies available quota helpers for codex, claude, copilot, and zai-backed engines. Per-engine coverage matches the acceptance criteria: each file has a fresh-run smoke test asserting the expected reply token appears in the parsed transcript, and continuation coverage is present for engines that support it. Codex, claude, copilot, gemini, and opencode use the unified latest-session continue sentinel; goz uses explicit resume-by-id via captured continuation data, which matches its adapter contract. Documentation is in place: tests_integration/README.md explains the tests/ vs tests_integration/ split, the HERU_INTEGRATION_ENGINES and HERU_INTEGRATION_TIMEOUT_SECONDS env vars, skip behavior, and the expected local proof command 'HERU_INTEGRATION_ENGINES=codex uv run pytest tests_integration/test_codex.py -q'. CLAUDE.md now documents the default fixture-only tests/ suite versus the opt-in real-binary tests_integration/ suite. Validation I reran in this review: 'uv run pytest tests/ -q' -> 234 passed; 'uv run pytest tests_integration/test_codex.py -q' with HERU_INTEGRATION_ENGINES unset -> 2 skipped; 'cd ~/git/litehive && uv run pytest tests/test_runner_workflow.py tests/test_engine_variants_and_timeline.py tests/test_heru_cli.py tests/test_codex_quota.py -q' -> 197 passed. I also inspected helpers.py and the per-engine files directly to confirm the skip logic, subprocess launch path, and continuation assertions. I did not run an opted-in authenticated real-engine smoke in this environment because HERU_INTEGRATION_ENGINES remained intentionally unset and engine availability/quota are machine-specific, but the required focused command is documented and the opt-in gating behaves correctly. Acceptance criteria are satisfied.\\\"\"","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
